A motorcyclist died after being knocked over by a bakkie in Womderboom South in Pretoria on Sunday afternoon‚ paramedics reported. Netcare 11 spokesman Shawn Herbst said that the emergency service had responded to reports of a collision on Steve Biko Road at about 12.15pm. “Reports from the scene indicate that an adult male was struck down by a one-ton delivery vehicle. “The patient unfortunately sustained life threatening injuries and was declared deceased on the scene‚” he said.